HEADWORD: Santon
<hw>San"ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>santon</ets>, augmented fr. <ets>santo</ets> holy, L.
<ets>sanctus</ets>.]</ety> <def>A Turkish saint; a kind of dervish,
regarded by the people as a saint: also, a hermit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

